    {
      "type": "CommentSubheading",
      "title": "Terms used to describe the Most Holy Place",
      "precomment": "",
      "refgroups": [
        {
          "type": "ReferenceGroup",
          "primaryrefs": [],
          "secondaryrefs": [
            {
              "type": "Reference",
              "refclass": "B",
              "comment": "``the Most Holy Place'' (or ``Holy of Holies''), in contrast to the ``Holy Place'' where the altar stood. This superlative suggests increasing closeness to the presence of God. The distinction is not always observed, however. In Leviticus chapter 16 ``Holy Place'' is used regularly (translated in NIV as ``Most Holy Place'' in verses 2, 16, 17, 20, 27, and as ``sanctuary area'' in verse 3, though it is the inner sanctuary that is referred to, as the phrase ``behind the curtain'' (verse 2) shows)",
              "continuation": false,
              "bcvreferences": [
                "02026033"
              ],
              "parallels": []
            },
            {
              "type": "Reference",
              "refclass": "B",
              "comment": "the ``inner sanctuary'' in contrast to the outer",
              "continuation": true,
              "bcvreferences": [
                "11006016"
              ],
              "parallels": []
            },
            {
              "type": "Reference",
              "refclass": "B",
              "comment": "literally ``the second (tabernacle)'' in contrast to the first or outer",
              "continuation": true,
              "bcvreferences": [
                "58009007"
